<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="203" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,223,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[357,461,223,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">Holotype</typeStatus>
complete specimen, 
<quantity box="[717,788,223,248]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="203" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
long for 47 chaetigers, 
<quantity box="[1085,1192,224,248]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="203" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.30 mm</quantity>
wide. All 
<typeStatus box="[1329,1437,224,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">paratypes</typeStatus>
incomplete. Prostomium short, rectangular, distinctly broader than long, with four rounded, small eyes in trapezoidal arrangement, reddish, sometimes difficult to distinguish in preserved material. Antennae absent in all examined individuals (
<figureCitation box="[409,492,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1018,1040]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,997]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,997]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Exogone sophiae n. sp. Paratype (MSNP: P/001/SEM) a) Prostomium in dorsal view, showing the absence of antennae; b) anterior end in ventral view; c) anterior parapodia in ventral view; d) spiniger-like chaeta from chaetiger 2; e) falciger-like chaetae from chaetiger 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135686/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
). Palps long, broad, fused for their total length, with barely noticeable distal notch. Dorsal cirri very small, oval, slightly longer in the posterior region, lacking at chaetiger 2 (
<figureCitation box="[1219,1304,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1926,1948]" captionTargetBox="[172,1393,858,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1437,841,1905]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Exogone sophiae n. sp. Paratype (MSNP: P/0242/V) a) anterior end indorsal view. Holotype (MSNP:P/3879): b) pygidium in dorsal view; c) spiniger-like chaeta from chaetiger 5; d) compound falciger chaetae from chaetiger 5; e) dorsal simple chaeta.Scale-bar: a‒b: 0.20 mm; c‒d‒e: 7 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135684/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
). First four parapodia with 2 compound spiniger-like chaetae and 3–4 falcigers, after chaetiger 5 only 1 spiniger-like and 3 falcigers (
<figureCitation box="[264,347,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1018,1040]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,997]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,997]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Exogone sophiae n. sp. Paratype (MSNP: P/001/SEM) a) Prostomium in dorsal view, showing the absence of antennae; b) anterior end in ventral view; c) anterior parapodia in ventral view; d) spiniger-like chaeta from chaetiger 2; e) falciger-like chaetae from chaetiger 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135686/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
). Anterior spiniger-like compound chaetae with thick, distally spinulous shaft (
<figureCitation box="[1244,1330,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1926,1948]" captionTargetBox="[172,1393,858,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1437,841,1905]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Exogone sophiae n. sp. Paratype (MSNP: P/0242/V) a) anterior end indorsal view. Holotype (MSNP:P/3879): b) pygidium in dorsal view; c) spiniger-like chaeta from chaetiger 5; d) compound falciger chaetae from chaetiger 5; e) dorsal simple chaeta.Scale-bar: a‒b: 0.20 mm; c‒d‒e: 7 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135684/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">Figs 3c</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1343,1375,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1018,1040]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,997]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,997]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Exogone sophiae n. sp. Paratype (MSNP: P/001/SEM) a) Prostomium in dorsal view, showing the absence of antennae; b) anterior end in ventral view; c) anterior parapodia in ventral view; d) spiniger-like chaeta from chaetiger 2; e) falciger-like chaetae from chaetiger 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135686/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">4d</figureCitation>
), and thin, elongated blades 25–35 µm long; blades sometimes slightly curved with several long teeth on basal part (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1926,1948]" captionTargetBox="[172,1393,858,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1437,841,1905]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Exogone sophiae n. sp. Paratype (MSNP: P/0242/V) a) anterior end indorsal view. Holotype (MSNP:P/3879): b) pygidium in dorsal view; c) spiniger-like chaeta from chaetiger 5; d) compound falciger chaetae from chaetiger 5; e) dorsal simple chaeta.Scale-bar: a‒b: 0.20 mm; c‒d‒e: 7 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135684/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">Figs 3c</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[193,224,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1018,1040]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,997]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,997]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Exogone sophiae n. sp. Paratype (MSNP: P/001/SEM) a) Prostomium in dorsal view, showing the absence of antennae; b) anterior end in ventral view; c) anterior parapodia in ventral view; d) spiniger-like chaeta from chaetiger 2; e) falciger-like chaetae from chaetiger 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135686/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">4d</figureCitation>
), difficult to see with the light microscope. Posterior spinigers-like chaetae similar but shorter and thinner, 15–20 µm long blades. Anterior falcigers with 7.5–10 µm long blade, with very small distal tooth, massive, strong proximal tooth, and relatively short, coarse serration along ventral edge (
<figureCitation box="[984,1072,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1926,1948]" captionTargetBox="[172,1393,858,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1437,841,1905]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Exogone sophiae n. sp. Paratype (MSNP: P/0242/V) a) anterior end indorsal view. Holotype (MSNP:P/3879): b) pygidium in dorsal view; c) spiniger-like chaeta from chaetiger 5; d) compound falciger chaetae from chaetiger 5; e) dorsal simple chaeta.Scale-bar: a‒b: 0.20 mm; c‒d‒e: 7 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135684/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">Figs 3d</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1086,1116,584,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1018,1040]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,997]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,997]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Exogone sophiae n. sp. Paratype (MSNP: P/001/SEM) a) Prostomium in dorsal view, showing the absence of antennae; b) anterior end in ventral view; c) anterior parapodia in ventral view; d) spiniger-like chaeta from chaetiger 2; e) falciger-like chaetae from chaetiger 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135686/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">4e</figureCitation>
). Posterior falcigers shorter, blades 3.8–5 µm long, with thicker basal part. Anterior dorsal simple chaetae unidentate, smooth; posterior dorsal simple chaetae become distinctly thicker, with a subdistal notch (
<figureCitation box="[889,971,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1926,1948]" captionTargetBox="[172,1393,858,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1437,841,1905]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Exogone sophiae n. sp. Paratype (MSNP: P/0242/V) a) anterior end indorsal view. Holotype (MSNP:P/3879): b) pygidium in dorsal view; c) spiniger-like chaeta from chaetiger 5; d) compound falciger chaetae from chaetiger 5; e) dorsal simple chaeta.Scale-bar: a‒b: 0.20 mm; c‒d‒e: 7 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135684/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
). Ventral simple chaetae absent. Pharynx long, relatively wide, extending through six chaetigers, with a large, triangular distal tooth. Proventricle barrelshaped, as long as pharynx, with 20–23 muscle cell rows. Pygidium sub-triangular with two very long, tapering anal cirri (
<figureCitation box="[266,350,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1926,1948]" captionTargetBox="[172,1393,858,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1437,841,1905]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Exogone sophiae n. sp. Paratype (MSNP: P/0242/V) a) anterior end indorsal view. Holotype (MSNP:P/3879): b) pygidium in dorsal view; c) spiniger-like chaeta from chaetiger 5; d) compound falciger chaetae from chaetiger 5; e) dorsal simple chaeta.Scale-bar: a‒b: 0.20 mm; c‒d‒e: 7 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135684/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
