is chiefly characterised by the absence of antennae; albeit preservation may cause the loss of antennae in some syllid species, we believe that this character is not a preservation artefact, as all the sampled individuals do not show any trace of antennae, nor of scars indicating the lost of antennae. Moreover, dorsal cirri are perfectly preserved, suggesting that preservation should not have altered the soft appendages of the collected specimens. Until now two species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Orsted" authorityYear="1845" box="[679,777,1359,1382]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[679,777,1359,1382]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">Exogone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without prostomial antennae have been described, namely 
<taxonomicName box="[151,344,1395,1418]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="acerata">
<emphasis box="[151,344,1395,1418]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">Exogone acerata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="San" box="[354,682,1394,1418]" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" refString="San Martin, G. &amp; Parapar, J. (1990) Exogone acerata n. sp. (Exogoninae: Syllidae: Polychaeta), a new species without antennae from the Mediterranean Sea. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 103, 687 - 690." type="journal article" year="1990">San Martín &amp; Parapar, 1990</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hartman &amp; Fauchald, 1971)" authorityName="Hartman &amp; Fauchald" authorityYear="1971" baseAuthorityName="Hartman &amp; Fauchald" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[747,1282,1394,1419]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis box="[747,939,1394,1419]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">Exogone oculata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hartman" box="[956,1274,1394,1419]" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" refString="Hartman, O. &amp; Fauchald, K. (1971) Deep-water benthic polychaetous annelids off New England to Bermuda and other North Atlantic Areas. Part II. Allan Hancock Monographs in Marine Biology, 6, 1 - 327." type="journal article" year="1971">Hartman &amp; Fauchald, 1971</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(San Martín, 1991). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Langeneck &amp; Musco &amp; Busoni &amp; Conese &amp; Aliani &amp; Castelli" authorityYear="2018" box="[230,349,1430,1455]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sophiae">
<emphasis box="[230,349,1430,1455]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">E. sophiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[497,614,1431,1454]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="acerata">
<emphasis box="[497,614,1431,1454]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">E. acerata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the absence of dorsal cirri at chaetiger 2 (present in 
<taxonomicName box="[1232,1349,1431,1454]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="acerata">
<emphasis box="[1232,1349,1431,1454]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">E. acerata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), in the less pronounced spinulation on shafts of spiniger-like chaetae and in the longer spines on blades of spiniger-like chaetae (
<bibRefCitation author="San" box="[253,588,1502,1527]" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" refString="San Martin, G. &amp; Parapar, J. (1990) Exogone acerata n. sp. (Exogoninae: Syllidae: Polychaeta), a new species without antennae from the Mediterranean Sea. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 103, 687 - 690." type="journal article" year="1990">San Martín &amp; Parapar, 1990</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Langeneck &amp; Musco &amp; Busoni &amp; Conese &amp; Aliani &amp; Castelli" authorityYear="2018" box="[611,806,1502,1527]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sophiae">
<emphasis box="[611,806,1502,1527]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">Exogone sophiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears closer to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hartman &amp; Fauchald" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[1023,1141,1502,1527]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis box="[1023,1141,1502,1527]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">E. oculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as both species lack the dorsal cirrus at chaetiger 2, but 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hartman &amp; Fauchald" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[513,629,1538,1563]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis box="[513,629,1538,1563]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">E. oculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks spiniger-like chaetae on the first four chaetigers. Moreover, both species are provided of ventral simple chaetae, that are absent in all examined individuals of the new species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1140,2031]" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">
Among Mediterranean species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Langeneck &amp; Musco &amp; Busoni &amp; Conese &amp; Aliani &amp; Castelli" authorityYear="2018" box="[559,679,1610,1635]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sophiae">
<emphasis box="[559,679,1610,1635]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">E. sophiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears particularly close to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Claparede, 1868)" authorityName="Claparede" authorityYear="1868" baseAuthorityName="Claparede" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[1016,1436,1610,1635]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="verugera">
<emphasis box="[1016,1224,1611,1634]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">Exogone verugera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Claparede" box="[1240,1428,1610,1635]" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" refString="Claparede, E. (1868) Les annelides chetopodes du Golfe de Naples. Memories de la Societe de Physique et d'Histoire Naturelle de Geneve, 19, 313 - 584." type="journal article" year="1868">Claparède, 1868</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Webster, 1879)" authorityName="Webster" authorityYear="1879" baseAuthorityName="Webster" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[200,568,1646,1671]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="dispar">
<emphasis box="[200,379,1646,1671]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">Exogone dispar</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Webster" box="[395,559,1646,1671]" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" refString="Webster, H. E. (1879) The Annelida Chaetopoda of the Virginian coast. Transactions of the Albany Institute, 9, 202 - 269." type="journal article" year="1879">Webster, 1879</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in size and overall body shape and number of proventricle cell rows. Apart from the absence of antennae, this species differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Claparede" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[770,902,1683,1706]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="verugera">
<emphasis box="[770,902,1683,1706]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">E. verugera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Langeneck &amp; Musco &amp; Busoni &amp; Conese &amp; Aliani &amp; Castelli" authorityYear="2018" box="[939,1057,1682,1707]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sophiae">
<emphasis box="[939,1057,1682,1707]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">E. sophiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has smaller, non-coalescent eyes, longer blades of falciger chaetae, with a higher number of marginal teeth, and slightly shorter blades of spinigerlike chaetae with a more pronounced spinulation along the ventral edge; moreover 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Langeneck &amp; Musco &amp; Busoni &amp; Conese &amp; Aliani &amp; Castelli" authorityYear="2018" box="[1085,1203,1754,1779]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sophiae">
<emphasis box="[1085,1203,1754,1779]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">E. sophiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks ventral simple chaetae. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Webster" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[253,435,1790,1815]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="dispar">
<emphasis box="[253,435,1790,1815]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">Exogone dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has similar blades of falciger chaetae, and a more pronounced spinulation along the ventral edge of spiniger-like blades (
<bibRefCitation author="San" box="[579,787,1826,1850]" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" refString="San Martin, G. (2003) Anelidos Poliquetos. Familia Syllidae Grube, 1850. Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CSIC, Madrid, 554 pp." type="book" year="2003">San Martín, 2003</bibRefCitation>
); however, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Langeneck &amp; Musco &amp; Busoni &amp; Conese &amp; Aliani &amp; Castelli" authorityYear="2018" box="[956,1077,1826,1851]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sophiae">
<emphasis box="[956,1077,1826,1851]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">E. sophiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
such spinulation is even more pronounced (
<figureCitation box="[304,393,1862,1887]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1926,1948]" captionTargetBox="[172,1393,858,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1437,841,1905]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Exogone sophiae n. sp. Paratype (MSNP: P/0242/V) a) anterior end indorsal view. Holotype (MSNP:P/3879): b) pygidium in dorsal view; c) spiniger-like chaeta from chaetiger 5; d) compound falciger chaetae from chaetiger 5; e) dorsal simple chaeta.Scale-bar: a‒b: 0.20 mm; c‒d‒e: 7 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135684/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">Fig. 3d</figureCitation>
). Moreover, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Webster" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[547,655,1862,1887]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="dispar">
<emphasis box="[547,655,1862,1887]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">E. dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has dorsal cirri at the second chaetiger. Lastly, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Langeneck &amp; Musco &amp; Busoni &amp; Conese &amp; Aliani &amp; Castelli" authorityYear="2018" box="[1235,1358,1862,1887]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sophiae">
<emphasis box="[1235,1358,1862,1887]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">E. sophiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might resemble 
<taxonomicName authorityName="San Martín, Ceberio &amp; Aguirrezabalaga" authorityYear="1996" box="[261,436,1898,1923]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="lopezi">
<emphasis box="[261,436,1898,1923]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">Exogone lopezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="San" box="[446,981,1898,1923]" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" refString="San Martin, G., Ceberio, A. &amp; Aguirrezabalaga, F. (1996) Exogone species (Polychaeta: Syllidae: Exogoninae) from the Capbreton Canyon (Bay of Biscay, NE Atlantic). Cahiers de Biologie Marine, 37, 249 - 258." type="journal article" year="1996">San Martín, Ceberio &amp; Aguirrezabalaga, 1996</bibRefCitation>
, since this last species apparently lacks ventral simple chaetae, and has very small antennae that are difficult to see. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="San Martín, Ceberio &amp; Aguirrezabalaga" authorityYear="1996" box="[1112,1210,1934,1959]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="lopezi">
<emphasis box="[1112,1210,1934,1959]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">E. lopezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has falciger chaetae with long, thread-like marginal teeth that outgrow the chaetal tip, whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Langeneck &amp; Musco &amp; Busoni &amp; Conese &amp; Aliani &amp; Castelli" authorityYear="2018" box="[1029,1148,1970,1995]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="7" pageNumber="204" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sophiae">
<emphasis box="[1029,1148,1970,1995]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">E. sophiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the marginal serration of falcigers is coarser and less developed.
</paragraph>
